learning_outcomes.en:
The student who has completed the course:
- recognises and values the fundamental connection between past, present and future in educational research and practice;
- is aware of different interpretations of the spatial and temporal categories of globalisation and trends in educational research; is able to critically reflect on her/his own research accordingly, noticing perspectives and limitations;
- understands and takes into account the dialectics between continuity and change in educational research and practice; 
- is aware of different interpretations of the relationship between history and education; recognises the value of history for understanding and making meaning of future developments in educational research and practices;
- recognises the basic similarities and differences between the Anglophone and Continental European educational traditions, is aware of the perspectives and limitations of her/his own research accordingly;
- is able to consciously distinguish between the spatial categories of global, regional and national in educational research; is able to take into account these different levels in her/his own research.

learning_outcomes.et:
Kursuse läbinud üliõpilane: 
- omab esmast ülevaadet paradigma ja selle muutumise mõistest haridus- ja kasvatusteadustes, suudab eristada retoorika muutumist ja sisulisi muutusi hariduspraktikas ja -teoorias;
- omab esmast ülevaadet haridusteaduste kui iseseisva distsipliini arenguloo käigus toimunud ja toimuvatest peamistest murrangutest;
- omab esmast ülevaadet Lääne kultuuriruumi hariduspraktika arenguloo käigus toimunud ja toimuvatest peamistest murrangutest;
- suudab oma teadus-, õppe- ja arendustegevuses tasakaalustatult arvestada ja rakendada traditsioone ja püsiväärtusi ning uuenduslikkust/innovaatilisust;
- mõistab, eristab ja suudab tasakaalustatult arvesse võtta globaalset, regionaalset ja eesti rahvuslikku tasandit oma teadus-, õppe- ja arendustegevuses.
